01:10:43,204 --> 01:10:47,243
Ha-ha! I see you!
Go get 'em, boy!

1258
01:10:47,346 --> 01:10:49,624
[LAUGHS]

1259
01:10:49,728 --> 01:10:51,316
[UPBEAT SONG PLAYING]

1260
01:11:05,330 --> 01:11:10,542
Whoa! Yeah, let's do this!
Marge! Give me five.

1261
01:11:10,645 --> 01:11:14,200
[LAUGHS] Jerry!
You're a madman. Pound me.

1262
01:11:17,445 --> 01:11:19,216
I thought it was supposed to
be more without the split.

1263
01:11:19,240 --> 01:11:24,176
Did you check for
other claims? Yes. There was one.

1264
01:11:24,280 --> 01:11:26,558
Where? Sunderland.

1265
01:11:26,661 --> 01:11:28,249
Shit!

1266
01:11:28,353 --> 01:11:31,148
He called your bluff, okay? There's
nothing we can do but accept it.

1267
01:11:31,252 --> 01:11:33,185
If there's a roll down,
he's going to play.

1268
01:11:34,359 --> 01:11:37,120
Unless we create
the roll down. What?

1269
01:11:37,223 --> 01:11:39,191
It takes weeks for
a roll down, right?

1270
01:11:39,295 --> 01:11:41,883
I mean, WinFall takes
in 100 grand a day,

1271
01:11:41,987 --> 01:11:44,667
and then when it hits two million,
we know a roll down is coming in,

1272
01:11:44,748 --> 01:11:47,924
and everybody starts betting, and
Benjamin Button gets in his truck.

1273
01:11:48,027 --> 01:11:52,135
But if we create a roll down when
nobody expects it, we take it all.

1274
01:11:52,238 --> 01:11:54,033
We squeeze the other
players out.

1275
01:11:54,137 --> 01:11:56,208
We use our hack
to track the pot,

1276
01:11:56,312 --> 01:11:58,900
we wait for it to hit
a million before a drawing,

1277
01:11:59,004 --> 01:12:01,938
and then we bet a million in one
day. I mean, we own the game.

1278
01:12:02,041 --> 01:12:04,872
And where do we get $1 million?

1279
01:12:08,324 --> 01:12:11,257
As you can see
by our returns, it works.

1280
01:12:11,361 --> 01:12:13,846
And with more capital,
we can control the game.

1281
01:12:13,950 --> 01:12:15,503
Is your dad in on this?

1282
01:12:16,159 --> 01:12:18,195
No. He... Um...

1283
01:12:18,299 --> 01:12:20,646
Thinks you're going to college?

1284
01:12:20,750 --> 01:12:23,373
He thinks I'm studying
to be a lawyer, like him.

1285
01:12:23,477 --> 01:12:27,204
But last time I checked, my father
never made $1 million in a night.

1286
01:12:31,036 --> 01:12:32,658
We have 14 hours
to pull this off.

1287
01:12:32,762 --> 01:12:35,223
Get to your location and don't
leave until you print all your tickets.

1288
01:12:35,247 --> 01:12:38,492
Some locations might push back
on printing all day, but do not let them.

1289
01:12:38,595 --> 01:12:39,631
They work for us.

1290
01:12:39,734 --> 01:12:40,735
Let's ride.

1291
01:12:40,839 --> 01:12:41,839
GIRL: Yes! BOY 1: Whoo!

1292
01:12:42,772 --> 01:12:43,772
BOY 2: Yeah.

1293
01:12:45,430 --> 01:12:48,881
Hey. What happens
if somebody wins the jackpot

1294
01:12:48,985 --> 01:12:51,297
and we lose $1 million?

1295
01:12:51,401 --> 01:12:54,439
Beyond dropping out of school
because I blew my entire tuition?

1296
01:12:55,819 --> 01:12:57,901
I think one of those investors
might actually kill me.

1297
01:12:57,925 --> 01:12:59,927
JERRY: Ooh.

1298
01:13:00,030 --> 01:13:02,447
You all right? JERRY: Yeah, I got it.

1299
01:13:02,550 --> 01:13:04,587
Oh. Okay.

1300
01:13:06,589 --> 01:13:07,693
I got the key.

1301
01:13:07,797 --> 01:13:08,936
[HORN HONKING]

1302
01:13:09,039 --> 01:13:10,420
What the heck?

1303
01:13:11,663 --> 01:13:12,767
MARGE: Oh.

1304
01:13:12,871 --> 01:13:14,251
BILL: Hey!

1305
01:13:15,252 --> 01:13:16,322
We missed it!

1306
01:13:16,426 --> 01:13:19,049
What, someone actually
hit all six numbers?

1307
01:13:19,153 --> 01:13:20,396
No. No. It rolled down.

1308
01:13:20,499 --> 01:13:22,915
No, that's impossible.
It's only the second week.

1309
01:13:23,019 --> 01:13:24,814
It never rolls down
before three.

1310
01:13:24,917 --> 01:13:27,195
It rolled down last night,
and we missed it.

1311
01:13:30,647 --> 01:13:33,201
The Harvard group
triggered it on their own.

1312
01:13:33,305 --> 01:13:34,996
MARGE: How would they know
how much to bet?

1313
01:13:35,100 --> 01:13:37,171
The lottery doesn't post
the amount...

1314
01:13:37,274 --> 01:13:38,862
Well, they knew.

1315
01:13:39,863 --> 01:13:40,864
Jerry?

1316
01:13:43,488 --> 01:13:44,868
Where are you going, Jerry?

1317
01:13:47,112 --> 01:13:48,596
[CAR DOOR CLOSES]Jerry!

1318
01:14:21,077 --> 01:14:24,287
TYLER: It's on the freakin' news.
The lottery didn't even see it coming.

1319
01:14:24,390 --> 01:14:26,358
This is so epic.[ERIC LAUGHS]

1320
01:14:28,671 --> 01:14:29,775
Hey, Jerry.

1321
01:14:29,879 --> 01:14:31,812
What, did you come ridin' in
on your tractor

1322
01:14:31,915 --> 01:14:33,296
to come give me a whoopin'?

1323
01:14:33,399 --> 01:14:35,712
Believe me, I wanted to.

1324
01:14:37,300 --> 01:14:38,853
Part of me still does.

1325
01:14:41,200 --> 01:14:45,135
But then on the long drive here,

1326
01:14:45,239 --> 01:14:48,760
well, most of that just,
poof, went away.

1327
01:14:48,863 --> 01:14:52,488
And I realized that I wasn't
really angry at you.

1328
01:14:53,178 --> 01:14:55,007
I'm disappointed.

1329
01:14:55,111 --> 01:14:56,699
Aw, you're disappointed in me?

1330
01:14:56,802 --> 01:14:59,011
No, not you.
You're insignificant.

1331
01:14:59,115 --> 01:15:05,501
No, I was disappointed that I let a
selfish kid like you get to me. Huh.

1332
01:15:05,604 --> 01:15:08,849
I was always good with math,

1333
01:15:08,952 --> 01:15:14,371
but it took a long time for me
to figure people out.

1334
01:15:14,475 --> 01:15:18,099
So, tell us, Jerry,
what did you figure out?

1335
01:15:18,203 --> 01:15:21,413
That the solution isn't numbers.

1336
01:15:21,517 --> 01:15:27,315
You told me that I was playing the
lottery because I had nothing else.

1337
01:15:27,419 --> 01:15:34,875
But the reason you won't share the
pot is because you have nothing else.

1338
01:15:34,978 --> 01:15:39,396
You think being the smartest
guy in the room is all that matters.

1339
01:15:39,500 --> 01:15:44,988
But it turns out
it's this room that matters.

1340
01:15:45,092 --> 01:15:49,855
All these bright, young people
helping you get rich.

1341
01:15:52,271 --> 01:15:55,378
How are you helping them?

1342
01:15:55,481 --> 01:15:58,933
Guess you haven't
run the math out on that, huh?

1343
01:15:59,037 --> 01:16:00,348
[STUDENTS MURMURING]

1344
01:16:01,108 --> 01:16:04,456
Anyway... my tractor's running.

1345
01:16:08,702 --> 01:16:10,807
I wish you all the best of luck.

1346
01:16:15,225 --> 01:16:16,813
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

1347
01:16:20,645 --> 01:16:23,475
What? Just get
back to counting.

1348
01:16:25,477 --> 01:16:30,344
If the Harvard team can trigger
a roll down, they run the game.

1349
01:16:30,447 --> 01:16:32,001
So we trigger our own roll down.

1350
01:16:32,104 --> 01:16:33,692
Yeah, we have enough cash.

1351
01:16:33,796 --> 01:16:34,900
No.Why?

1352
01:16:35,004 --> 01:16:37,731
Because it's not fair
to the regular players.

1353
01:16:37,834 --> 01:16:39,491
He's right.
It's not who we are.

1354
01:16:39,595 --> 01:16:40,734
But we're so close.

1355
01:16:40,837 --> 01:16:43,357
I mean, downtown is back,
the jazz fest is coming.

1356
01:16:43,460 --> 01:16:46,060
If we keep winning, we could
actually hire somebody to play there.

1357
01:16:46,118 --> 01:16:47,292
You should get Steely Dan.

1358
01:16:47,395 --> 01:16:49,984
That is an amazing idea.
We should get Steely Dan.

1359
01:16:50,088 --> 01:16:51,952
We can't win if we can't play.

1360
01:16:52,055 --> 01:16:53,505
Well, this just sucks.

1361
01:16:53,609 --> 01:16:56,888
The lottery isn't stopping us,
but a bunch of college kids are?

1362
01:16:56,991 --> 01:17:00,408
Huh, that's a good point. What is? I wasn't
making a point.

1363
01:17:00,512 --> 01:17:03,653
Why isn't the lottery
stopping them?

1364
01:17:03,757 --> 01:17:06,207
It's because they don't care.

1365
01:17:07,243 --> 01:17:08,485
Oh.

1366
01:17:09,107 --> 01:17:10,487
That could be our answer.

1367
01:17:16,079 --> 01:17:20,774
Always happy to meet with our
loyal players, Mr. and Mrs. Selbee.

1368
01:17:20,877 --> 01:17:24,156
Oh, please. "Jerry
and Marge" is fine.

1369
01:17:25,226 --> 01:17:26,266
What can we help you with?

1370
01:17:26,331 --> 01:17:27,504
JERRY: So here's the thing.

1371
01:17:27,608 --> 01:17:31,474
The state lottery was losing
money a few years ago,

1372
01:17:31,577 --> 01:17:33,718
and hardly anybody
was winning the jackpot,

1373
01:17:33,821 --> 01:17:37,583
so Mega Millions ate your lunch.

1374
01:17:37,687 --> 01:17:40,897
Then along comes WinFall,
and all that changes.

1375
01:17:41,001 --> 01:17:43,037
You folks made millions,

1376
01:17:43,141 --> 01:17:47,248
before you realized
there was a flaw in the math.

1377
01:17:48,215 --> 01:17:50,700
You probably panicked at first,

1378
01:17:50,804 --> 01:17:53,669
because you knew that
once everybody saw it,

1379
01:17:53,772 --> 01:17:56,188
that the game would collapse.

1380
01:17:56,292 --> 01:17:58,294
Except they didn't see it.

1381
01:17:58,397 --> 01:18:01,711
Only me and a few kids
from Harvard.

1382
01:18:01,815 --> 01:18:05,094
Which meant that we were
pushing millions into the game,

1383
01:18:05,197 --> 01:18:08,235
and, boy, sent your profits
through the roof.

1384
01:18:09,788 --> 01:18:15,104
So, all of a sudden, your
mistake became your windfall.

1385
01:18:15,207 --> 01:18:16,484
I gave him that line.

1386
01:18:16,588 --> 01:18:18,970
Yeah, she sure did,
and it's a dandy.[ALL CHUCKLE]

1387
01:18:20,350 --> 01:18:22,076
So, what exactly do you want?

1388
01:18:22,180 --> 01:18:24,113
Transparency.

1389
01:18:24,216 --> 01:18:29,601
We'd like the website to show
the size of the jackpot.

1390
01:18:29,705 --> 01:18:33,225
That prevents any group
from forcing a roll down.

1391
01:18:34,364 --> 01:18:37,264
Makes it fair for anybody
who plays.

1392
01:18:37,367 --> 01:18:42,372
And we would like two machines
at the Liquor Hut in Sunderland.

1393
01:18:42,476 --> 01:18:43,960
So we can be together.

1394
01:18:45,410 --> 01:18:47,239
These are our golden years.

1395
01:18:53,763 --> 01:18:55,178
We'll take care of it.

1396
01:18:56,110 --> 01:18:58,043
Yeah, we'll be making
another play soon.

1397
01:18:59,424 --> 01:19:03,117
That's great
to hear. Yeah. Talk soon.

1398
01:19:03,221 --> 01:19:05,026
He's wants to bring in
other partners from the firm.

1399
01:19:05,050 --> 01:19:06,707
Dude, we might not
ever need a real job.

1400
01:19:06,811 --> 01:19:08,502
They posted the jackpot. What?

1401
01:19:08,605 --> 01:19:12,437
The lottery changed the website.
You can track the jackpot online.

1402
01:19:12,540 --> 01:19:14,025
We can't roll it down anymore.

1403
01:19:14,128 --> 01:19:16,130
Shit. Shit.

1404
01:19:17,097 --> 01:19:19,824
All right, let's break this guy.

1405
01:19:19,927 --> 01:19:21,653
He wants a war?
We'll give him one.

1406
01:19:22,585 --> 01:19:24,276
[FOOTSTEPS RECEDING]

1407
01:19:24,380 --> 01:19:26,140
[MACHINES WHIRRING]

1408
01:19:30,593 --> 01:19:33,976
You want some nachos? Uh, no.

1409
01:19:34,079 --> 01:19:35,287
Yeah, I'll try some.

1410
01:19:38,428 --> 01:19:40,051
You know, I'm good.

1411
01:19:50,751 --> 01:19:52,246
Where is everyone?
We're supposed to be betting.

1412
01:19:52,270 --> 01:19:56,550
Dude, it's over.
Nobody wants to do it anymore.

1413
01:19:56,653 --> 01:19:58,034
What? Why? We're winning.

1414
01:19:58,138 --> 01:20:00,692
No. We're assholes.

1415
01:20:00,796 --> 01:20:03,005
And that doesn't work
for anybody but you.

1416
01:20:04,834 --> 01:20:07,216
Fine. I'll do it on my own.

1417
01:20:11,082 --> 01:20:12,082
[DOOR SLAMS]

1418
01:20:13,636 --> 01:20:15,155
[MACHINE WHIRRING]

1419
01:20:24,371 --> 01:20:26,062
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

1420
01:20:27,408 --> 01:20:28,824
GIRL 1: It's gonna be insane.

1421
01:20:29,445 --> 01:20:30,826
GIRL 2: Crazy.

1422
01:20:30,929 --> 01:20:33,138
BOY 1: I told you
we should have...

1423
01:20:33,242 --> 01:20:35,042
BOY 2: Did you get
the pretzels? GIRL 3: Yeah.

1424
01:20:39,144 --> 01:20:41,422
This just came for you. Thank you.

1425
01:20:41,526 --> 01:20:43,183
Oh. Finally.

1426
01:20:44,391 --> 01:20:45,633
Paycheck?

1427
01:20:45,737 --> 01:20:48,188
[SCOFFS] Like I'd get
excited about that.

1428
01:20:48,291 --> 01:20:51,570
No. State lottery commission.

1429
01:20:51,674 --> 01:20:53,089
They don't want to talk to me,

1430
01:20:53,193 --> 01:20:56,334
but anybody that wins above
60,000 is in the public record.

1431
01:20:56,437 --> 01:20:58,129
You just have to
submit a request.

1432
01:20:58,232 --> 01:21:02,409
Which I did, for every drawing
in the last six months.

1433
01:21:03,479 --> 01:21:07,069
Gerald Selbee,
every three weeks.

1434
01:21:10,106 --> 01:21:11,106
Mmm-hmm.

1435
01:21:11,832 --> 01:21:13,213
MARTIN: Tyler Langford.

1436
01:21:15,318 --> 01:21:16,423
Same drawings.

1437
01:21:17,493 --> 01:21:18,839
There's another one.

1438
01:21:21,221 --> 01:21:22,878
Huh.

1439
01:21:22,981 --> 01:21:27,606
Tyler Langford.
Tyler Langford.

1440
01:21:27,710 --> 01:21:30,713
Okay, Tyler Langford, I see you.

1441
01:21:33,440 --> 01:21:36,581
Best euro I've ever spent.

1442
01:21:36,684 --> 01:21:38,203
Thanks, Raj. RAJ: Thank you.

1443
01:21:38,307 --> 01:21:39,308
Okay, girl.

1444
01:21:44,244 --> 01:21:45,693
Darn! JERRY: Whoa!

1445
01:21:45,797 --> 01:21:47,385
Try one more time, sweetheart.

1446
01:21:47,488 --> 01:21:48,973
Like a kangaroo.[JERRY LAUGHS]

1447
01:21:49,076 --> 01:21:51,389
Hey, would you
hand me a 10 mil? Yeah.

1448
01:21:53,253 --> 01:21:54,771
Ten mil.

1449
01:21:55,496 --> 01:21:56,808
Here you go. Thank you.

1450
01:21:56,912 --> 01:21:58,672
You won't even buy
yourself a new truck?

1451
01:21:58,775 --> 01:22:00,398
Nah. This one works.

1452
01:22:00,501 --> 01:22:01,778
Does it?

1453
01:22:01,882 --> 01:22:04,885
Not all the time. But I think
that's why I like it.

1454
01:22:04,989 --> 01:22:05,989
Hmm.

1455
01:22:06,749 --> 01:22:08,026
You know what?

1456
01:22:09,200 --> 01:22:10,511
I did buy this.

1457
01:22:11,443 --> 01:22:13,100
[CHUCKLES]

1458
01:22:16,483 --> 01:22:21,867
I counted nickels with you because
it was something I understood.

1459
01:22:23,973 --> 01:22:27,701
I didn't know a better way
to spend time with you.

1460
01:22:27,804 --> 01:22:29,806
I just knew that I wanted to.

1461
01:22:34,915 --> 01:22:36,399
You know how it works?

1462
01:22:36,503 --> 01:22:40,956
Well, I assume you create
spin, which gives it a third axis,

1463
01:22:41,059 --> 01:22:44,373
so that the wind can
offset the gravity.

1464
01:22:45,995 --> 01:22:48,066
Yeah, that's it.
Just like that.

1465
01:22:50,620 --> 01:22:52,277
Wanna test that theory?

1466
01:22:52,381 --> 01:22:53,416
All right.

1467
01:22:53,520 --> 01:22:55,073
Fingers on the laces.Yeah.

1468
01:22:57,973 --> 01:22:59,388
Oh, well. Not bad.

1469
01:22:59,491 --> 01:23:02,356
I'll work it out. I know you will.

1470
01:23:03,737 --> 01:23:06,050
Oh, that's it. MAYA: Mr. Selbee?

1471
01:23:06,912 --> 01:23:09,122
Maya Jordon. Boston Globe.

1472
01:23:10,571 --> 01:23:14,334
I'd like to ask you some questions
about GS Investment Strategies.

1473
01:23:16,508 --> 01:23:22,928
So, you and your wife count
tickets in a hotel room for 11 days?

1474
01:23:23,032 --> 01:23:24,068
Yup.

1475
01:23:24,447 --> 01:23:25,828
[CHUCKLES]

1476
01:23:25,931 --> 01:23:28,555
That's so much work.

1477
01:23:30,419 --> 01:23:31,799
Mmm.

1478
01:23:31,903 --> 01:23:34,319
It doesn't seem like work.

1479
01:23:34,423 --> 01:23:36,425
I've worked all my life.

1480
01:23:37,288 --> 01:23:39,014
This is different.

1481
01:23:40,463 --> 01:23:42,431
This is very different.

1482
01:23:56,652 --> 01:23:58,481
You send it in yet?

1483
01:23:58,585 --> 01:24:00,587
They helped their entire town.

1484
01:24:01,657 --> 01:24:03,107
The flaw isn't the story.

1485
01:24:03,210 --> 01:24:05,350
Well, this can't be
a puff piece.

1486
01:24:05,902 --> 01:24:07,214
I need a headline.

1487
01:24:17,845 --> 01:24:20,296
[ENGINE STOPS]Ah.

1488
01:24:20,400 --> 01:24:25,612
[SIGHS] well, we do well on this
one, we won't need the game anymore.

1489
01:24:25,715 --> 01:24:26,923
You know, I was thinking,

1490
01:24:27,027 --> 01:24:29,305
if we're going to have
a fund for the town,

1491
01:24:29,409 --> 01:24:31,721
managing it, it's gonna be
a full-time job.

1492
01:24:31,825 --> 01:24:33,689
Well...

1493
01:24:33,792 --> 01:24:38,487
Hey, you think we can get one of
those offices downtown, like Steve's?

1494
01:24:38,590 --> 01:24:40,144
[SNICKERS]What?

1495
01:24:40,247 --> 01:24:42,146
I already got us one
right next to his.

1496
01:24:42,249 --> 01:24:43,802
You did? [LAUGHS]Yes!

1497
01:24:43,906 --> 01:24:47,116
In fact, his Corvette is actually
in one of our parking spots.

1498
01:24:47,220 --> 01:24:49,222
JERRY: Well, we'll have to
take care of that.

1499
01:24:49,325 --> 01:24:51,810
MARGE: What? They're moving out
the WinFall machine.

1500
01:24:51,914 --> 01:24:53,329
Hey, hey! Hey. Hey!

1501
01:24:55,849 --> 01:24:59,749
Hey. Bill! Bill,
what happened?

1502
01:24:59,853 --> 01:25:01,820
The lottery suspended
our license.

1503
01:25:01,924 --> 01:25:04,064
Why? You didn't see the article?

1504
01:25:08,275 --> 01:25:09,483
MARGE: Oh.

1505
01:25:17,905 --> 01:25:20,149
Hey, buddy. How's school? Uh, Dad.

1506
01:25:20,253 --> 01:25:22,255
What are you doing here? You're famous.

1507
01:25:24,602 --> 01:25:26,224
Great move, genius.

1508
01:25:26,328 --> 01:25:28,640
Let's go. Pack up your stuff.
You're coming home.

1509
01:25:29,814 --> 01:25:31,126
Now.

1510
01:25:33,921 --> 01:25:36,821
The high-volume betting groups
discovered a flaw in the game

1511
01:25:36,924 --> 01:25:40,273
and took advantage of it, to
the tune of millions of dollars.

1512
01:25:40,376 --> 01:25:42,999
Lottery officials expressed
their surprise at the discovery

1513
01:25:43,103 --> 01:25:46,693
and announced they will phase
out the game after tonight's drawing.

1514
01:25:46,796 --> 01:25:48,488
Moving on to our next...[TV STOPS]

1515
01:25:48,591 --> 01:25:52,595
The last roll down was today.
You could've gotten your final win.

1516
01:25:55,184 --> 01:25:59,015
Yes. But even if
we found a place to bet,

1517
01:25:59,119 --> 01:26:01,294
it wouldn't have felt the same.

1518
01:26:03,606 --> 01:26:04,952
[MARGE GRUNTS]

1519
01:26:05,056 --> 01:26:07,645
It was more than
just a game to him.

1520
01:26:12,374 --> 01:26:15,687
He finally got to use his gift
to connect to people.

1521
01:26:17,206 --> 01:26:18,656
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

1522
01:26:21,072 --> 01:26:22,522
[SIGHS]

1523
01:26:23,350 --> 01:26:24,593
[HONKING]

1524
01:26:26,491 --> 01:26:27,491
Jerry!

1525
01:26:28,597 --> 01:26:29,701
What?

1526
01:26:29,805 --> 01:26:31,127
The shareholders
are having a meeting tonight

1527
01:26:31,151 --> 01:26:33,636
and were wondering if
you could stop by.

1528
01:26:33,740 --> 01:26:34,948
Are they upset?

1529
01:26:35,051 --> 01:26:37,088
If I told you that,
you wouldn't come.

1530
01:26:40,264 --> 01:26:42,744
JERRY: I tried to answer all
their questions in the newsletter.

1531
01:26:42,818 --> 01:26:44,854
I don't think they know
how to open the newsletter.

1532
01:26:44,958 --> 01:26:47,132
Well, they don't have to
worry about anything.

1533
01:26:47,236 --> 01:26:49,065
We didn't break any laws.

1534
01:26:52,345 --> 01:26:56,176
Holy... It's jazz fest? What?

1535
01:26:56,280 --> 01:26:58,765
MAN: Jerry! Marge! JERRY: Huh.

1536
01:26:59,697 --> 01:27:01,526
MAN: Yeah!

1537
01:27:03,666 --> 01:27:05,012
[CHEERING AND APPLAUSE]

1538
01:27:05,116 --> 01:27:06,738
BILL: Come on!

1539
01:27:06,842 --> 01:27:08,326
Let's do this!

1540
01:27:12,882 --> 01:27:15,851
Yeah! Okay, right?

1541
01:27:15,954 --> 01:27:18,267
Jer and Marge!

1542
01:27:18,371 --> 01:27:22,167
How did you...
We missed the final play.

1543
01:27:22,271 --> 01:27:23,617
Oh, no, we did not.

1544
01:27:23,721 --> 01:27:26,206
Yeah, everybody took a store,
Dad. All across the state.

1545
01:27:26,310 --> 01:27:28,035
We had a bus and everything.

1546
01:27:28,139 --> 01:27:29,830
What? Oh.

1547
01:27:29,934 --> 01:27:31,246
You didn't have to do that.

1548
01:27:31,349 --> 01:27:33,386
You did it for us.
Why wouldn't we do it for you?

1549
01:27:33,489 --> 01:27:36,665
And don't worry, we left
you two the counting part.

1550
01:27:37,907 --> 01:27:39,495
[JERRY LAUGHS]

1551
01:27:41,601 --> 01:27:43,361
Hey, Raj!

1552
01:27:43,465 --> 01:27:45,605
I would help,
but, uh, I can't count.

1553
01:27:45,708 --> 01:27:49,436
HOWARD: Yes, you can. I can
count. I just don't like to count.

1554
01:27:49,540 --> 01:27:52,543
This town isn't just a newspaper
article, Jerry. It's all of us.

1555
01:27:52,646 --> 01:27:54,924
And you brought this town
back from the dead

1556
01:27:55,028 --> 01:27:58,514
when nobody else could, because
you don't think we're just numbers.

1557
01:28:00,861 --> 01:28:02,277
No. No.

1558
01:28:02,898 --> 01:28:04,244
You're family.

1559
01:28:05,452 --> 01:28:06,636
ANNOUNCER OVER MICROPHONE:
Ladies and gentlemen,

1560
01:28:06,660 --> 01:28:12,079
please put your hands together
for Tori Kelly!

1561
01:28:12,183 --> 01:28:17,361
♪ Stars shining bright
Above you

1562
01:28:17,464 --> 01:28:22,366
♪ Night breezes seem
To whisper "I love you..."

1563
01:28:22,469 --> 01:28:23,643
Shall we?

1564
01:28:23,746 --> 01:28:25,092
It is jazz fest.

1565
01:28:25,196 --> 01:28:27,509
♪ Birds singing in the
Sycamore tree

1566
01:28:27,612 --> 01:28:32,272
♪ Dream a little dream of me

1567
01:28:33,687 --> 01:28:38,727
♪ Say nighty-night
And kiss me

1568
01:28:38,830 --> 01:28:44,319
♪ Just hold me tight
And tell me you'll miss me

1569
01:28:44,422 --> 01:28:48,840
♪ While I'm alone and blue
As can be

1570
01:28:48,944 --> 01:28:52,844
♪ Dream a little dream of me

1571
01:28:54,743 --> 01:28:59,782
♪ Stars fading
But I linger on, dear...

1572
01:29:00,990 --> 01:29:03,303
Hey, Steve. Hey, Rhoda.

1573
01:29:03,407 --> 01:29:06,168
Hey, you know, I've been working
on that Eat, Pray, Love trip for you.

1574
01:29:06,271 --> 01:29:07,342
I got some great rates.

1575
01:29:07,445 --> 01:29:09,999
Ooh. That's exciting.
Thank you.Yeah.

1576
01:29:10,103 --> 01:29:11,898
Yeah, sure.

1577
01:29:12,001 --> 01:29:15,280
Um, do you want to dance?

1578
01:29:15,384 --> 01:29:18,870
Um, yeah. I mean, do you?

1579
01:29:18,974 --> 01:29:21,183
Yes. That's why I asked.

1580
01:29:21,286 --> 01:29:25,394
Right. That does make
sense.[CHUCKLES] Yeah.

1581
01:29:26,153 --> 01:29:27,258
Okay.

1582
01:29:27,362 --> 01:29:31,607
♪ But in your dreams
Whatever they be

1583
01:29:31,711 --> 01:29:35,887
♪ Dream a little dream
Of me...

1584
01:29:37,544 --> 01:29:40,547
How badly do you want to go
and just count all those tickets?

1585
01:29:40,651 --> 01:29:41,997
Mmm.

1586
01:29:42,100 --> 01:29:45,518
JERRY: It's taking everything
in me not to do it right now.

1587
01:29:45,621 --> 01:29:48,452
I'm going to miss it. Yeah, yeah.

1588
01:29:49,729 --> 01:29:50,833
Me, too.

1589
01:29:51,765 --> 01:29:52,870
[EXHALES]

1590
01:29:52,973 --> 01:29:56,805
I kinda wish we'd won
the jackpot. Just once.

1591
01:29:58,220 --> 01:30:01,396
I won the jackpot
before we ever started.

1592
01:30:01,499 --> 01:30:06,987
♪ Stars fading
But I linger on, dear

1593
01:30:07,091 --> 01:30:11,544
♪ Still craving your kiss...

1594
01:30:11,647 --> 01:30:14,167
BILL: Jerry and Marge
dissolved our betting group

1595
01:30:14,270 --> 01:30:17,342
when the WinFall game
was phased out.

1596
01:30:17,446 --> 01:30:21,416
They used most of their lottery winnings
to start a construction loan business

1597
01:30:21,519 --> 01:30:23,659
for the town of Evart.

1598
01:30:23,763 --> 01:30:25,363
Like many of their friends
and neighbors,

1599
01:30:25,454 --> 01:30:28,940
they also put their children and
grandchildren through school.

1600
01:30:30,114 --> 01:30:34,429
I myself invested
in a very luxurious man cave.

1601
01:30:34,532 --> 01:30:36,016
Whoo! Ah!

1602
01:30:36,120 --> 01:30:39,434
BILL: Jerry did finally give in
and buy himself a new truck,

1603
01:30:39,537 --> 01:30:41,746
which was actually
slightly used,

1604
01:30:41,850 --> 01:30:44,749
because he calculated
that was a smarter purchase.

1605
01:30:44,853 --> 01:30:46,233
And he would know.

1606
01:30:46,337 --> 01:30:52,964
His lottery calculation won
a grand total of $27 million.

1607
01:30:53,068 --> 01:30:55,208
Okay, let's go count.

1608
